data.title: Mrs. Doubtfires (Robin Williams) Face Mold Set
data.meta_description: Mrs. Doubtfires (Robin Williams) face molds from Chris Columbus family comedy Mrs. Doubtfire. Having lost custody of his children, voice-over actor Daniel Hillard (Williams) dons prosthetic make-up to embody an elderly housekeeper so he can spend time with his kids.pThe set consists of five epoxy molds used to cast the facial appliances used to transform Williams into the lovable nanny. The molds consists of positive and negative castings of the chin, eye bags, lower lip, right eyelid and lip. Each mold is also labelled for facial part.p This set shows some wear to the epoxy due to production use and age, however the set remains in fine used condition.
